share with you.

00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:23.600
The first thing is
it's hard to make

00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:25.390
good decisions with
incomplete date

00:10:25.390 --> 00:10:26.640
or just one kind of persona.

00:10:26.640 --> 00:10:28.900
So if you can
research real users,

00:10:28.900 --> 00:10:31.770
and especially think about
entire tribes of users,

00:10:31.770 --> 00:10:34.199
dig into that and
identify your community.

00:10:34.199 --> 00:10:35.240
MICHAEL AUSTIN SUI: Nice.

00:10:35.240 --> 00:10:35.530
Love that.

00:10:35.530 --> 00:10:36.030
All right.

00:10:36.030 --> 00:10:38.390
So once you've got your
community identified--

00:10:38.390 --> 00:10:41.420
those people are full of
passion and personality.

00:10:41.420 --> 00:10:43.780
So why not look to
them to help define

00:10:43.780 --> 00:10:45.800
your product and your brand.

00:10:45.800 --> 00:10:48.460
JOSH SASSOON: And next if you've
identified your community it's

00:10:48.460 --> 00:10:51.060
way way, way more fun to design
with them instead of just

00:10:51.060 --> 00:10:51.560
for them.

00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:53.770
So engage with the
tribes on your platform

00:10:53.770 --> 00:10:54.960
as often as you can.

00:10:54.960 --> 00:10:56.752
Talk to your users
and communities.

00:10:56.752 --> 00:10:57.710
MICHAEL AUSTIN SUI: OK.

00:10:57.710 --> 00:10:58.390
Love that.

